{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"31b05a32-be3f-4cd0-afc9-550bd7c808e1","content":"Here's what you need for NativeAOT crash dump collection with `createdump`:\n\n**Environment variables** (on your container):\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                          # Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage)\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/core.%t.%p\"      # %t=timestamp, %p=PID\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"       # Required — NativeAOT can't auto-discover it\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add: [\"SYS_PTRACE\"]           # createdump needs ptrace access\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi                  # size to your memory limit\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** is critical for NativeAOT — the runtime won't find `createdump` on its own since there's no standard runtime install layout.\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required; without it `createdump` will fail silently.\n- Use a **PersistentVolumeClaim** instead of `emptyDir` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- Consider a sidecar or CronJob to ship dumps out (e.g., to blob storage) before the volume fills up.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"570899cb-49ea-4014-8254-8609e6115d47","outputTokens":453,"requestId":"DA17:2DDEB2:22C1D03:267B09F:6A03D8CC"},"id":"6fa1c9b9-d37d-48bc-ac96-9a40a0e7deb4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:50:13.663Z","parentId":"d13f9d2d-e01c-4171-b72a-baecefe6350e"}
